VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT start_ip_address\s*=\s*"0\.0\.0\.0"[^}]*end_ip_address\s*=\s*"0\.0\.0\.0"
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:start_ip_address\s*=\s*"0\.0\.0\.0".*end_ip_address\s*=\s*"0\.0\.0\.0" && MISSING:# intentional|# development|firewall_rule
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects Azure SQL firewall rules using the 0.0.0.0/0.0.0.0 pattern that allows all Azure services to connect.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Azure SQL Server Allows All Azure Services.
